function lookUpByName(name)
    local all = getAllObjects()
    for each, obj in pairs (all) do
        if(obj.getName()==name) then
            return obj
        end
    end

    print("Couldn't find: "..name)
    return nil
end

function updateRoundsSlider(player, value, id)
  UI.setValue('playerValue', '' ..value )
end

faceDown = {0.00, 180.00, 180.00}
faceUp = {5.00, 180.00, 0.00}
faceDown2 = {0.00, 0.00, 180.00}
faceUp2 = {5.00, 0.00, 0.00}

bags = {"c8f90d"}
useColony = false

trashBag = {
  pos = {-17.5,3,1}
}

PlayerDecks = {

}

Players = {
  player1 = {
    pos = {4.5, 1, -10.5},
    number = 0
  },
  player2 = {
    pos = {-24, 1, -10.5},
    number = 1
  },
  player3 = {
    pos = {23, 1, 12},
    number = 2
  },
  player4 = {
    pos = {-5.5, 1, 12},
    number = 3
  }
}

function setup()
    if #bags == 0 then
      print("You have to select at least one base or expansion")
      return
    end

    print("Setting up for " .. UI.getValue('playerValue') .. " players")
    UI.hide("setupMenu")

    for each, player in pairs (Players) do
      if player.number < tonumber(UI.getValue('playerValue')) then
        table.insert(PlayerDecks, 1, player)
      end
    end

    for each, deck in pairs (PlayerDecks) do
        component = lookUpByName("estate")
        for i=1,3 do
          if deck.number == 0 or deck.number == 1 then
            waitfor(giveCard,{component,deck,faceDown},(i*10))
          else
            waitfor(giveCard,{component,deck,faceDown2},(i*10))
          end
          time = (i*10)+(deck.number*60)
        end
        component = lookUpByName("copper")
        for i=1,7 do
          if deck.number == 0 or deck.number == 1 then
            waitfor(giveCard,{component,deck,faceDown},(i*10))
          else
            waitfor(giveCard,{component,deck,faceDown2},(i*10))
          end
        end

    end

    if UI.getValue('playerValue') == "2" then
      component = lookUpByName("curse")
      for i=1,20 do
        waitfor(giveCard,{component,trashBag,faceUp},(180)+(i*2))
      end
      component = lookUpByName("colony")
      for i=1,4 do
        waitfor(giveCard,{component,trashBag,faceUp},(180)+(i*10))
      end
      component = lookUpByName("province")
      for i=1,4 do
        waitfor(giveCard,{component,trashBag,faceUp},(180)+(i*10))
      end
      component = lookUpByName("duchy")
      for i=1,4 do
        waitfor(giveCard,{component,trashBag,faceUp},(180)+(i*10))
      end
      component = lookUpByName("estate")
      for i=1,10 do
        waitfor(giveCard,{component,trashBag,faceUp},(180)+(i*4))
      end
    end

    if UI.getValue('playerValue') == "3" then
      component = lookUpByName("curse")
      for i=1,10 do
        waitfor(giveCard,{component,trashBag,faceUp},(180)+(i*4))
      end
      component = lookUpByName("estate")
      for i=1,3 do
        waitfor(giveCard,{component,trashBag,faceUp},(180)+(i*10))
      end
    end

    waitfor(getKingdoms,nil,300)
    waitfor(getDecks,nil,500)

end

function getKingdoms()
  if useColony then
    component = lookUpByName("platinum")
    component.flip()
    component = lookUpByName("colony")
    component.flip()
  end

  for i=1,10 do
    rng = math.random(1,#bags)
    bag = getObjectFromGUID(bags[rng])
    name = "kingdom " .. i
    kingdom = {pos = lookUpByName(name).getPosition() }
    waitfor(giveCard,{bag,kingdom,faceUp},(i*10))
  end

end

function getDecks()
  objects = getAllObjects()
  for each, obj in pairs (objects) do
    if obj.is_face_down and obj.getQuantity() == 10 then
      obj.shuffle()
    end
  end
end

function giveCard(component,deck,rotation)
  pos = Vector(deck.pos)
  card = component.takeObject()
  card.setPositionSmooth({pos.x,pos.y+2,pos.z}, false, false)
  card.setRotationSmooth(rotation, false, false)
end

function waitfor(fun,args,frames)
  Wait.frames(
  function()
    if args != nil then
      fun(unpack(args))
    else
      fun()
    end
  end
  ,frames)
end

function print(text)
  broadcastToAll(tostring(text))
end

function addGame(player,value,id)
  if value == "True" then
    table.insert(bags, 1, id)
  else
    for each, obj in pairs(bags) do
      if obj == id then
        table.remove(bags, each)
      end
    end
  end
end

function colony(player,value,id)
  if value == "True" then
    useColony = true
  else
    useColony = false
  end
end
